{"word":"H6473 - פָּעַר - pâʻar - paw-ar' - Gape","slug":"H6473","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">פָּעַר</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>pâʻar"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>paw-ar'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Gape"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E4;&#x05BC;&#x05E2;&#x05E8; - pa&#x0302;&#x201B;ar</b> - <i>paw-ar'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>yawn</i>, that is, <i>open</i> wide (literally or figuratively): - gape, open (wide)."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H6465\">H6465</a>, <a href=\"#/H6474\">H6474</a>"}]}